@agtmadcat @siliconvalleycf Of the sources investigated, the Parcel Tax would raise the least revenue - $20m-$156m annually depending on how it was set.  Other revenue sources that had greater potential included the Business Parking Levy and the VMT Tax. A combination of sources may be ultimately required.

@siliconvalleycf We were happy to participate in the Advisory Group for this study alongside @MTCBATA and Voices for Public Transportation coalition members @Urban_Habitat and @wpusanews. We support an equitable regional transportation funding measure.

New report from @siliconvalleycf shows there are promising, more equitable options to raise $$$ for transit investments, including: 

1. Head tax on large employers
2. Parcel tax 
3. Surcharge on upper income tax brackets
4. Business parking levy
5. VMT Tax https://t.co/2FhrXgOaqb
